Nomura Sees Bank of England Resuming Asset Purchases in November

-- B y   S c o t t   H a m i l t o n
-- 
2011-09-29T14:08:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/nomura-sees-bank-of-england-resuming-asset-purchases-in-november.html
Nomura International Plc sees the
 Bank of England  restarting bond purchases in November, it said
today.  The central bank will announce an initial 50 billion pounds
of purchases in November and a further 25 billion pounds in
February, economists including Philip Rush in  London  said in an
e-mailed note.  Nomura also forecasts that the Bank of England will keep
its benchmark  interest rate  at a record-low 0.5 percent until
August 2013.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Hamilton in London at 
